<section xml:id="C10.S54">
<title>Integral Representations</title>        
  
<para xml:id="C10.S54.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="10.54.1" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S54.E1">\mathsf{j}_{n}\left(z\right)=\frac{z^{n}}{2^{n+1}n!}\int_{0}^{\pi}\cos\left(z \cos\theta\right)(\sin\theta)^{2n+1}\mathrm{d}\theta</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.54.2" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S54.E2">\mathsf{j}_{n}\left(z\right)=\frac{(-i)^{n}}{2}\int_{0}^{\pi}e^{iz\cos\theta}P _{n}\left(\cos\theta\right)\sin\theta\mathrm{d}\theta</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="10.54.3" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S54.E3">\mathsf{k}_{n}\left(z\right)=\frac{\pi}{2}\int_{1}^{\infty}e^{-zt}P_{n}\left(t \right)\mathrm{d}t, if |\operatorname{ph}z|&lt;\tfrac{1}{2}\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="10.54.4" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S54.E4">\mathsf{j}_{n}\left(z\right)=\frac{(-i)^{n+1}}{2\pi}\int_{i\infty}^{(-1+,1+)}e ^{izt}Q_{n}\left(t\right)\mathrm{d}t, if |\operatorname{ph}z|&lt;\tfrac{1}{2}\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="10.54.5" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S54.E5">{\mathsf{h}^{(1)}_{n}}\left(z\right)=\frac{(-i)^{n+1}}{\pi}\int_{i\infty}^{(1+ )}e^{izt}Q_{n}\left(t\right)\mathrm{d}t,{\mathsf{h}^{(2)}_{n}}\left(z\right)=\frac{(-i)^{n+1}}{\pi}\int_{i\infty}^{(-1 +)}e^{izt}Q_{n}\left(t\right)\mathrm{d}t, if |\operatorname{ph}z|&lt;\tfrac{1}{2}\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.s6">
For the Legendre polynomial <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.m1">P_{n}</Math> and the associated Legendre function <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.m2">Q_{n}</Math> see §§18.3 and 14.21(i), with <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.m3">\mu=0</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S54.p1.m4">\nu=n</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S54.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C10.S54.p2.s1">
Additional integral representations can be obtained by combining the definitions (10.47.3)–(10.47.9) with the results given in §10.9 and §10.32.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</section>
